str2: Therefore, then. Apparently a primary word; certainly, or accordingly.
Pilate. Of Latin origin; close-pressed, i.e. Firm; Pilatus, a Roman.

str2: To go out, come out. From ek and erchomai; to issue.

To, towards, with. A strengthened form of pro; a preposition of direction; forward to, i.e. Toward.

str2: He, she, it, they, them, same. From the particle au; the reflexive pronoun self, used of the third person, and of the other persons.

str2: To say, declare. Properly, the same as the base of phos and phaino; to show or make known one's thoughts, i.e. Speak or say.

str2: Who, which, what, why. Probably emphatic of tis; an interrogative pronoun, who, which or what.

str2: To carry, bear, bring; I conduct, lead; perhaps: I make publicly known. A primary verb.

A man, one of the human race. From aner and ops; man-faced, i.e. A human being.
